# /usr/share/ollama/.keep
#
# Placeholder so `git reset --hard` materializes /usr/share/ollama/
# on the dev-overlay seed path that bypasses the OCI build. The
# ollama.container Quadlet bind-mounts this directory read-only into
# the container at the same path:
#
#     Volume=/usr/share/ollama:/usr/share/ollama:ro,Z
#
# On a normally-built MiOS image, automation/37-ollama-prep.sh has
# baked the configured model set into ./models/ before this file is
# read. On MiOS-DEV (the WSL2 dev VM seeded via build-mios.ps1), the
# build prep step never runs, so this directory would otherwise be
# absent and `podman run` would fail with:
#
#     Error: statfs /usr/share/ollama: no such file or directory
#
# Keeping a single tracked .keep file under each tier (this dir +
# models/) is the minimum tracked-content that survives a
# `reset --hard` and reproduces the on-disk surface the Quadlet
# expects.
